<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-05T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-05T16:00:00-05:00" n="183" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d183">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/114<hi rend="superscript">1/12</hi>: Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Nicholson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-05T15:00:00-06:00">June 5, 1940—3 p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 5:15
                                        p.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>51. Department’s strictly confidential telegram No. 39, June 3, 3
                                        p.m.<note n="3" xml:id="d183fn1">See footnote 29, <ref target="#pg_16">p. 16</ref>.</note> President Somoza is
                                    in full agreement with the principles expressed in the telegram
                                    under reference and cordially offers the complete cooperation of
                                    the Nicaraguan Government.</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Nicholson</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>